         <div class="order-1 md:order-2 space-y-6">
           <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-heading text-slate-900 leading-tight">
              Drop Deck Trailer
           </h2>
           <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              A <strong>drop deck trailer</strong>, also known as a step-deck, is designed to haul tall or oversized cargo that exceeds standard height limits. It features two deck levels upper and lower and an open structure with no roof, sides, or rear doors, allowing flexible loading and transport of heavy or irregularly shaped equipment.
           </p>
         </div>
      </div>

       <!-- Section 7: Tanker -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-20">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-heading text-slate-900 leading-tight">
             Tanker trailer
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              A <strong>tanker trailer</strong> is designed to safely transport liquids or dry bulk materials. Its internal compartments allow multiple substances like fuel, milk, or chemicals to be hauled in a single load.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="relative h-full" data-aos="fade-left">
           <img src="/img/tankertrailer.webp" width="640" height="480" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl w-full object-cover" alt="heavy haul transport tank trailer"/>
        </div>
      </div>

       <!-- Section 8: Flatbed -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-20">
         <div class="order-2 md:order-1 relative h-full" data-aos="fade-right">
           <img src="/img/flatbed.webp" width="2016" height="1512" class="rounded-2xl shadow-2xl w-full object-cover" alt="heavy haul shipping flatbed"/>
         </div>
         <div class="order-1 md:order-2 space-y-6">
           <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold font-heading text-slate-900 leading-tight">
              Flatbed Trailer
           </h2>
           <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
              A <strong>flatbed trailer</strong> is an open-deck trailer with no sides or roof, ideal for hauling oversized, wide, or heavy cargo like machinery and construction materials. Its flat design allows for easy loading and unloading from any angle.
           </p>
         </div>
